               <p>WILLIAS JONES. I am a ship-joiner in the employ of Mr. 
               <persName id="t18330214-29-person416">
                  Thomas 
                  Snook
               <interp inst="t18330214-29-person416" type="surname" value="Snook"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330214-29-person416" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330214-29-person416" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             - this copper is his property; <placeName id="t18330214-29-crimeloc171">the Montreal</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18330214-29-crimeloc171" type="placeName" value="the Montreal"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18330214-29-crimeloc171" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18330214-29-off169 t18330214-29-crimeloc171"></join> was in his dry dock - it belongs to Mr. Greig; the prisoner was quite a stranger - we lost copper from<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183302140030"></xptr>time to time; I was set to watch in the joiner's shop on the 11th of January - the men went to dinner at one o'clock, and about twenty minutes after I saw the prisoner come into the dock - he had no right there; he could not see me, as I was concealed - he pulled off a pea-jacket which he had on, then crossed the boom of the vessel, and went down into the dock; he came out again and crossed the boom - I jumped out, and took him about twenty yards before he got off the premises; I saw these two sheets of copper taken from him - I had seen him lurking about before he crossed the vessel, as if to see if he was observed.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18330214-29-person417">
                  RICHARD 
                  MILNER
               <interp inst="t18330214-29-person417" type="surname" value="MILNER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330214-29-person417" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330214-29-person417" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took the prisoner in the dock-yard, and found this copper under a round frock which he had on.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18330214-29-person418">
                  THOMAS 
                  MOODY
               <interp inst="t18330214-29-person418" type="surname" value="MOODY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330214-29-person418" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330214-29-person418" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I took the prisoner and this copper, which weighs 16 lbs.; I asked how he got it - he said a strange man gave it him; he said his name was Jones at the office, but I had seen him there before, and he gave his name as 
               <persName id="t18330214-29-person419">
                  Michael 
                  Collins
               <interp inst="t18330214-29-person419" type="surname" value="Collins"></interp>
